            <para>* Engine must be at normal operating temperature.</para>
            <para>Refer to "Performance Data Guidelines" in this section.</para>
            <para>Use either the Kent-Moore Tach-n-Time (ZTSE-4142), Creative Tool Tach/Time Kit CT-4000 (SE-2783 or
                3005A) or the Design Technology "Tech Time" Model 3354 as directed in Section 4, to determine injection
                pump initial timing and timing advance.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>IF THE ENGINE PERFORMANCE CHECKS INDICATE THAT THE INTAKE MANIFOLD PRESSURE AND ENGINE RPM AT
                        LOW AND HIGH IDLE ARE WITHIN THE PUBLISHED PERFORMANCE DATA GUIDELINE SPECIFICATIONS, TIMING
                        CHECKS SHOULD NOT BE REQUIRED.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <para>Advance Curves</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500525">5.25</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                shows the advance rates for the turbocharged engines used on OEM and On- Highway applications.
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500526">5.26</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                shows the advance rates for the DT-466B and DTI-466B engines used on On-Highway vehicles only.
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500527">5.27</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                shows the advance rates for DT and DTI-466B 1980 California engines.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When using the timing light, observed timing will be slightly less than initial timing plus
                        the automatic advance. This slight lag is caused by the time required for the fuel to travel
                        from the plunger through internal pump passages to the transducer.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Verify the engine model, horsepower and rated engine speed. Cross reference the injection pump part
                number (original equipment or ReNEWed) with those listed in the "Performance Data Guidelines," in this
                section.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>THE TIMING LIGHT'S PRIME PURPOSE IS TO DETERMINE IF THE ADVANCE UNIT IS OPERATING. STATIC
                        TIMING [ENGINE STOPPED]. SHOULD ONLY BE CHANGED AFTER VISUALLY INSPECTING THE INJECTION PUMP HUB
                        AND TIMING POINTER.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
